---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="hero-label">Creative Director &amp; Systems Strategist</p>
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        Design meets risk.<br />
        <em>Consequence before aesthetics.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        I help organizations build credible, strategic brands in politically
        complex environments &mdash; using systems thinking, AI infrastructure, and a
        deep understanding of how power shapes digital behavior.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-belief">
        Design without political awareness is complicity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <span class="label">What I do</span>
      <h2>Four domains. One lens.</h2>
      <div class="pillars">
        <div class="pillar">
          <p class="pillar-num">01</p>
          <h3>Systems of Power &amp; Digital Governance</h3>
          <p>How platforms govern behavior. How censorship shapes UX. How infrastructure encodes control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <p class="pillar-num">02</p>
          <h3>AI as Organizational Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Building AI creative teams. Designing workflows &mdash; not using tools. AI restructures labor; most people are still using it like a shortcut.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <p class="pillar-num">03</p>
          <h3>Brand Authority in High-Stakes Environments</h3>
          <p>Building institutional trust when your audience has every reason to be skeptical. Narrative control under pressure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <p class="pillar-num">04</p>
          <h3>Cognitive &amp; Emotional Engineering</h3>
          <p>The emotional economy of platforms. Attention as currency. Affect as a governance mechanism.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <span class="label">The constraint</span>
      <h2>A hard line.</h2>
      <div class="constraint">
        <p>
          <strong>I will not work for any organization that uses design &mdash; intentionally or structurally &mdash; to suppress, surveil, or control people.</strong>
          This is not a case-by-case judgment. It is a standing policy. The reason is experiential, not theoretical: I watched a brand I built get misused. I understand firsthand that design is a tool &mdash; and that the moral responsibility of the designer does not end at delivery.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
